"```sql\nSELECT district.A2 AS district_name\nFROM client\nJOIN disp ON client.client_id = disp.client_id\nJOIN account ON disp.account_id = account.account_id\nJOIN district ON account.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE client.gender = 'F' AND client.birth_date = '1976-01-29';\n```\nThis SQL query retrieves the district name where the female client, born on January 29, 1976, opened her account. It uses the provided schema, primary keys, and foreign key relationships to join the necessary tables and filter the results based on the specified conditions."